# grapher_templates_smoke.numos — open Grapher, start editing an empty first slot,
# open the Templates modal, screenshot it, and ASSERT Grapher is active.
#
# Phase 8P smoke (warning-only candidate; NO golden, NO mask in this phase).
# Exercises Grapher's Templates modal — the last major uncaptured Grapher surface.
#
# Flow (all verified in src/apps/GrapherApp.cpp):
#   * down  : TAB_BAR -> CONTENT; with _numFuncs=0 the selected row is the "Add an
#             element" row (_exprIdx==_numFuncs).
#   * enter : addFunction() -> startEditing() slot 0 (EDITING mode, empty AST).
#   * right : handleExprEdit RIGHT on an EMPTY expression opens the Templates modal
#             (GrapherApp.cpp:2263-2270 -> showTemplates(), GrapherApp.cpp:1390-1437).
#             RIGHT only opens templates while the slot AST is the single Empty node,
#             so this MUST run before any character is typed.
#   * showTemplates() draws the modal title "Templates" + 6 row shells, highlights the
#     first row, and starts a lazy AST loader (tplLoadTimerCb every TPL_LOAD_INTERVAL_MS
#     = 30ms, GrapherApp.cpp:1436/1444-1469) that fills one VPAM math preview per tick.
#     In --deterministic mode that timer fires by frame index, so after a generous wait
#     all six previews are loaded and the frame is stable / byte-identical run-to-run.
#
# Tofu: the modal is already tofu-free — the only plain label is the single-word title
# "Templates" (GrapherApp.cpp:1412, no space) and the rows render the template .text as
# VPAM math previews (GrapherApp.cpp:1457-1466), not plain prose; the bottom editor hint
# is already lv_font_montserrat_14 (Phase 8J). No GrapherApp label change was needed.
# (The sin(x)/cos(x) previews render small — a VPAM math-renderer behavior, not tofu and
# out of scope for this phase.)
#
# Determinism: run1-vs-run2 from fresh launches is byte-identical. The only
# wall-clock-volatile region is the StatusBar clock (HH:MM).
#
# All key tokens are already scriptable (down, enter, right) — no NativeHal change.
#
# Timing notes (deterministic, step-ms 16):
#   * 200 frames -> splash done; launcher.
#   *  60 frames -> Grapher load + fade settles.
#   * down,enter -> start editing the empty first slot.
#   *  40 frames -> editing UI settles.
#   * right      -> open the Templates modal + start the lazy AST loader.
#   * 150 frames -> all 6 lazy template previews loaded + modal settles.
#
# Run:
#   program --headless --deterministic --script tests/emulator/scripts/grapher_templates_smoke.numos \
#           --frames 800 --screenshot out/grapher_templates_smoke.ppm --quiet
# Exit codes: 0 ok · 2 script/parse error · 3 screenshot write error · 4 assertion failure.

log "grapher_templates_smoke: waiting for launcher"
wait 200

# Open Grapher (emulator launchApp id 1 — same id as the launcher's Grapher card).
open_app Grapher
wait 60

# Start editing the empty first slot (down -> Add row, enter -> addFunction/startEditing).
key down
key enter
wait 40

# Open the Templates modal: RIGHT on the still-empty expression -> showTemplates().
key right
wait 150

# Screenshot FIRST: the deferred capture happens on this frame, before the assert
# runs on a later frame, so the artifact is produced even if the assertion fails.
screenshot out/grapher_templates_smoke.ppm
log "grapher_templates_smoke: screenshot captured"

assert_app Grapher
log "grapher_templates_smoke: assertion passed (Grapher active, Templates modal)"
